            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>

    <ul>
    <li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PS4</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PS5</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a></li><li><a href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a></li>    </ul>

    
    <p><span>Milestone achieved just over seven months after relase.</span>
      </p></div><div><p>Total sales for slow-life <a title="Genres > RPG [17,915 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/rpg">RPG</a> <em><a title="Games > FANTASY LIFE i: The Girl Who Steals Time [42 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/games/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time">FANTASY LIFE i: The Girl Who Steals Time</a></em> have surpassed 1.5 million units, just over seven months after release, publisher <a title="Companies > LEVEL-5 [803 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/companies/level-5">LEVEL-5</a> and developer LEVEL-5 Osaka <a href="https://twitter.com/L5_fantasylife/status/2005592643376713751" target="_blank" rel="noopener">announced</a>. <span id="more-1017409"></span></p><figure><a data-featherlight="image" href="https://www.gematsu.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Fantasy-Life-i-Sales_12-29-25.jpg"></a></figure><p><em>FANTASY LIFE i: The Girl Who Steals Time</em> launched for <a title="Platforms > PS5 [11,139 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps5">PlayStation 5</a>, <a title="Platforms > Xbox Series [8,523 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/xbox/xbox-series">Xbox Series</a>, <a title="Platforms > PS4 [28,625 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/playstation/ps4">PlayStation 4</a>, <a title="Platforms > Switch [18,158 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch">Switch</a>, and <a title="Platforms > PC [25,187 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/pc">PC</a> via <a href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2993780/FANTASY_LIFE_i_The_Girl_Who_Steals_Time/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Steam</a> on May 21 worldwide, followed by <a title="Platforms > Switch 2 [845 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/platforms/nintendo/switch-2">Switch 2</a> on June 5. It sold <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/05/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-500000">500,000 copies</a> within its first two days of release, <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-800000">800,000 copies</a> within 10 days, <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/06/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-one-million">one million copies</a> by June 12, <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/07/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-1-2-million-switch-2-physical-edition-launches-august-7-in-japan">1.2 million copies</a> by July 7, and <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/09/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-1-4-million">1.4 million copies</a> by September 25.</p><p>The major free major update “The Sinister Broker Bazario’s Schemes” <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/12/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-free-major-update-the-sinister-broker-bazarios-schemes-now-available">launched</a> on December 24, introducing a new <a title="Genres > Roguelike [407 articles]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/genres/roguelike">roguelike game</a> mode where each run offers varied rewards that can be brought back to the main game.</p></div></div><br/><br/>https://www.gematsu.com/2025/12/fantasy-life-i-the-girl-who-steals-time-sales-top-1-5-million]]></content:encoded>
